Botswana Plans to Sell 2 1/2 Year Bond, Treasury Bills, Central Bank Says

-- B y   N i c o l a s   C .   F l e u r y
-- 
2011-03-03T14:42:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/botswana-plans-to-sell-2-1-2-year-bond-treasury-bills-central-bank-says.html
Botswana plans to sell 500 million
pula ($76 million) of 2 1/2 year bonds on March 11, the
Gaborone-based Bank of Botswana said in an e-mail today.  The bond, maturing on Sept. 11, 2013, will have a semi-
annual coupon of 7.25 percent, the central bank said. The bank
will also offer 2 billion pula of 182-day Treasury bills on the
same day.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicolas C Fleury in London at 
 nfleury3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  